api.name: on
api.description: When API event should occur

api.name: cache
api.description: Can be set to 'local' to cache successful returned AJAX responses when using a JSON API. This helps avoid server roundtrips when API endpoints will return the same results when accessed repeatedly. Setting to false, will add cache busting parameters to the URL.

api.name: stateContext
api.description: UI state will be applied to this element, defaults to triggering element.

api.name: encodeParameters
api.description: Whether to encode parameters with encodeURIComponent before adding into url string

api.name: defaultData
api.description: Whether to automatically include default data like {value} and {text}

api.name: serializeForm
api.description: Whether to serialize closest form and include in request

api.name: throttle
api.description: How long to wait when a request is made before triggering request, useful for rate limiting oninput

api.name: throttleFirstRequest
api.description: When set to false will not delay the first request made, when no others are queued

api.name: interruptRequests
api.description: Whether an API request can occur while another request is still pending

api.name: loadingDuration
api.description: Minimum duration to show loading indication

api.name: hideError
api.description: The default auto will automatically remove error state after error duration, unless the element is a form

api.name: errorDuration
api.description: Setting to true, will not remove error. Setting to a duration in milliseconds to show error state after request error.

api.name: action
api.description: Named API action for query, originally specified in $.fn.settings.api

api.name: url
api.description: Templated URL for query, will override specified action

api.name: urlData
api.description: Variables to use for replacement

api.name: response
api.description: Can be set to a Javascript object which will be returned automatically instead of requesting JSON from server

api.name: responseAsync(settings, callback)
api.description: When specified, this function can be used to retrieve content from a server and return it asynchronously instead of a standard AJAX call. The callback function should return the server response.

api.name: mockResponse
api.description: Alias of response

api.name: mockResponseAsync
api.description: Alias of responseAsync

api.name: method
api.description: Method for transmitting request to server

api.name: dataType
api.description: Expected data type of response

api.name: data
api.description: POST/GET Data to Send with Request

accordion.name: exclusive
accordion.description: Only allow one section open at a time

accordion.name: on
accordion.description: Event on title that will cause accordion to open

accordion.name: animateChildren
accordion.description: Whether child content opacity should be animated (may cause performance issues with many child elements)

accordion.name: close nested
accordion.description: Close open nested accordion content when an element closes

accordion.name: duration
accordion.description: Duration in ms of opening animation

accordion.name: easing
accordion.description: Easing of opening animation. EaseInOutQuint is included with accordion, for additional options you must include easing equations.

checkbox.name: uncheckable
checkbox.description: Setting to true/false will determine whether an input will allow no selection. Auto will set disallow this behavior only for radio boxes

checkbox.name: fireOnInit
checkbox.description: Whether callbacks for checked status should be fired on init as well as change

dimmer.name: opacity
dimmer.description: Dimmers opacity from 0-1. Defaults to auto which uses the CSS specified opacity.

dimmer.name: variation
dimmer.description: Specify a variation to add when generating dimmer, like inverted

dimmer.name: dimmerName
dimmer.description: If initializing a dimmer on a dimmable context, you can use dimmerName to distinguish between multiple dimmers in that context.

dimmer.name: closable
dimmer.description: Whether clicking on the dimmer should hide the dimmer (Defaults to auto, closable only when settings.on is not hover

dimmer.name: on
dimmer.description: Can be set to hover or click to show/hide dimmer on dimmable event

dimmer.name: useCSS
dimmer.description: Whether to dim dimmers using CSS transitions.

dimmer.name: duration
dimmer.description: Animation duration of dimming. If an integer is used, that value will apply to both show and hide animations.

dimmer.name: transition
dimmer.description: Named transition to use when animating menu in and out. Fade and slide down are available without including ui transitions

dropdown.name: on
dropdown.description: Event used to trigger dropdown (Hover, Click, Custom Event)

dropdown.name: allowReselection
dropdown.description: When set to true will fire onChange even when the value a user select matches the currently selected value.

dropdown.name: allowAdditions
dropdown.description: Whether search selection should allow users to add their own selections, works for single or multiselect.

dropdown.name: hideAdditions
dropdown.description: When disabled user additions will appear in the results menu using a specially formatted selection item formatted by templates.addition.

dropdown.name: action
dropdown.description: Sets a default action to occur. (See usage guide)

dropdown.name: minCharacters
dropdown.description: The minimum characters for a search to begin showing results

dropdown.name: match
dropdown.description: When using search selection specifies how to match values.

dropdown.name: selectOnKeydown
dropdown.description: Whether dropdown should select new option when using keyboard shortcuts. Setting to false will require enter or left click to confirm a choice.

dropdown.name: forceSelection
dropdown.description: Whether search selection will force currently selected choice when element is blurred.

dropdown.name: allowCategorySelection
dropdown.description: Whether menu items with sub-menus (categories) should be selectable

dropdown.name: placeholder
dropdown.description: auto: Convert option with "" (blank string) value to placeholder text, value: Sets string value to placeholder text, leaves "" value, false: Leaves "" value as a selectable option

dropdown.name: apiSettings
dropdown.description: Can be set to an object to specify API settings for retrieving remote selection menu content from an API endpoint

dropdown.name: fields
dropdown.description: List mapping dropdown content to JSON Property when using API

dropdown.name: saveRemoteData
dropdown.description: When enabled will automatically store selected name/value pairs in sessionStorage to preserve user selection on page refresh. Disabling will clear remote dropdown values on refresh.

dropdown.name: useLabels
dropdown.description: Whether multiselect should use labels. Must be set to true when allowAdditions is true

dropdown.name: maxSelections
dropdown.description: When set to a number, sets the maximum number of selections

dropdown.name: glyphWidth
dropdown.description: Maximum glyph width, used to calculate search size. This is usually size of a "W" in your font in em

dropdown.name: label
dropdown.description: Allows customization of multi-select labels

dropdown.name: direction
dropdown.description: When set to auto determines direction based on whether dropdown can fit on screen. Set to upward or downward to always force a direction.

dropdown.name: keepOnScreen
dropdown.description: Whether dropdown should try to keep itself on screen by checking whether menus display position in its context (Default context is page).

dropdown.name: context
dropdown.description: Element context to use when checking whether can show when keepOnScreen: true

dropdown.name: fullTextSearch
dropdown.description: Specifying to "true" will use a fuzzy full text search, setting to "exact" will force the exact search to be matched somewhere in the string

dropdown.name: preserveHTML
dropdown.description: Whether HTML included in dropdown values should be preserved. (Allows icons to show up in selected value)

dropdown.name: sortSelect
dropdown.description: Whether to sort values when creating a dropdown automatically from a select element.

dropdown.name: showOnFocus
dropdown.description: Whether to show dropdown menu automatically on element focus.

dropdown.name: allowTab
dropdown.description: Whether to allow the element to be navigable by keyboard, by automatically creating a tabindex

dropdown.name: transition
dropdown.description: Named transition to use when animating menu in and out. Defaults to slide down or slide up depending on dropdown direction. Fade and slide down are available without including ui transitions

dropdown.name: duration
dropdown.description: Duration of animation events

dropdown.name: keys
dropdown.description: The keycode used to represent keyboard shortcuts. To avoid issues with some foreign languages, you can pass false for comma delimiter's value

dropdown.name: delay
dropdown.description: Time in milliseconds to debounce show or hide behavior when on: hover is used, or when touch is used.

embed.name: icon
embed.description: Specifies an icon to use with placeholder content

embed.name: source
embed.description: Specifies a source to use, if no source is provided it will be determined from the domain of a specified url.

embed.name: url
embed.description: Specifies a url to use for embed

embed.name: id
embed.description: Specifies an id value to replace with the {id} value found in templated urls

embed.name: parameters
embed.description: Specify an object containing key/value pairs to add to the iframes GET parameters

embed.name: autoplay
embed.description: Default setting auto will only autoplay content when a placeholder is specified. Setting to true or false will force autoplay.

embed.name: color
embed.description: Specifies a default chrome color with Vimeo or YouTube.

embed.name: brandedUI
embed.description: Whether to show networks branded UI like title cards, or after video calls to action.

form.name: keyboardShortcuts
form.description: Adds keyboard shortcuts for enter and escape keys to submit form and blur fields respectively

form.name: on
form.description: Event used to trigger validation. Can be either submit, blur or change.

form.name: revalidate
form.description: If set to true will revalidate fields with errors on input change

form.name: delay
form.description: Delay from last typed letter to validate a field when using on: changeor when revalidating a field.

form.name: inline
form.description: Adds inline error on field validation error

form.name: transition
form.description: Named transition to use when animating validation errors. Fade and slide down are available without including ui transitions

modal.name: detachable
modal.description: If set to false will prevent the modal from being moved to inside the dimmer

modal.name: autofocus
modal.description: When true, the first form input inside the modal will receive focus when shown. Set this to false to prevent this behavior.

modal.name: observeChanges
modal.description: Whether any change in modal DOM should automatically refresh cached positions

modal.name: allowMultiple
modal.description: If set to true will not close other visible modals when opening a new one

modal.name: keyboardShortcuts
modal.description: Whether to automatically bind keyboard shortcuts

modal.name: offset
modal.description: A vertical offset to allow for content outside of modal, for example a close button, to be centered.

modal.name: context
modal.description: Selector or jquery object specifying the area to dim

modal.name: closable
modal.description: Setting to false will not allow you to close the modal by clicking on the dimmer

modal.name: dimmerSettings
modal.description: You can specify custom settings to extend UI dimmer

modal.name: transition
modal.description: Named transition to use when animating menu in and out, full list can be found in ui transitions docs.

popup.name: popup
popup.description: Can specify a DOM element that should be used as the popup. This is useful for including a pre-formatted popup.

popup.name: exclusive
popup.description: Whether all other popups should be hidden when this popup is opened

popup.name: movePopup
popup.description: Whether to move popup to same offset container as target element when popup already exists on the page. Using a popup inside of an element without overflow:visible, like a sidebar, may require you to set this to false

popup.name: observeChanges
popup.description: Whether popup should attach mutationObservers to automatically run destroy when the element is removed from the page's DOM.

popup.name: boundary
popup.description: When the popup surpasses the boundary of this element, it will attempt to find another display position.

popup.name: context
popup.description: Selector or jquery object specifying where the popup should be created.

popup.name: scrollContext
popup.description: Will automatically hide a popup on scroll event in this context

popup.name: jitter
popup.description: Number of pixels that a popup is allowed to appear outside the boundaries of its context. This allows for permissible rounding errors when an element is against the edge of its context.

popup.name: position
popup.description: Position that the popup should appear

popup.name: inline
popup.description: If a popup is inline it will be created next to current element, allowing for local css rules to apply. It will not be removed from the DOM after being hidden. Otherwise popups will appended to body and removed after being hidden.

popup.name: preserve
popup.description: Whether popup contents should be preserved in the page after being hidden, allowing it to re-appear slightly faster on subsequent loads.

popup.name: prefer
popup.description: Can be set to adjacent or opposite to prefer adjacent or opposite position if popup cannot fit on screen

popup.name: lastResort
popup.description: When set to false, a popup will not appear and produce an error message if it cannot entirely fit on page. Setting this to a position like, right center forces the popup to use this position as a last resort even if it is partially offstage. Setting this to true will use the last attempted position.

popup.name: on
popup.description: Event used to trigger popup. Can be either focus, click, hover, or manual. Manual popups must be triggered with $('.element').popup('show');

popup.name: delay
popup.description: Delay in milliseconds before showing or hiding a popup on hover or focus

popup.name: transition
popup.description: Named transition to use when animating menu in and out. Fade and slide down are available without including ui transitions

popup.name: duration
popup.description: Duration of animation events

popup.name: setFluidWidth
popup.description: Whether popup should set fluid popup variation width on load to avoid width: 100%including padding

popup.name: hoverable
popup.description: Whether popup should not close on hover (useful for popup navigation menus)

popup.name: closable
popup.description: When using on: 'click' specifies whether clicking the page should close the popup

popup.name: addTouchEvents
popup.description: When using on: 'hover' whether touchstart events should be added to allow the popup to be triggered

popup.name: hideOnScroll
popup.description: Whether popup should hide on scroll or touchmove, auto only hides for popups without on: 'click'.
Set this to false to prevent mobile browsers from closing popups when you tap inside input fields.

popup.name: target
popup.description: If a selector or jQuery object is specified this allows the popup to be positioned relative to that element.

popup.name: distanceAway
popup.description: Offset for distance of popup from element

popup.name: offset
popup.description: Offset in pixels from calculated position

popup.name: maxSearchDepth
popup.description: Number of iterations before giving up search for popup position when a popup cannot fit on screen

popup.name: variation
popup.description: Popup variation to use, can use multiple variations with a space delimiter

popup.name: content
popup.description: Content to display

popup.name: title
popup.description: Title to display alongside content

popup.name: html
popup.description: HTML content to display instead of preformatted title and content

progress.name: autoSuccess
progress.description: Whether success state should automatically trigger when progress completes

progress.name: showActivity
progress.description: Whether progress should automatically show activity when incremented

progress.name: limitValues
progress.description: When set to true, values that calculate to above 100% or below 0% will be adjusted. When set to false, inappropriate values will produce an error.

progress.name: label
progress.description: Can be set to either to display progress as percent or ratio. Matches up to corresponding text template with the same name.

progress.name: random
progress.description: When incrementing without value, sets range for random increment value

progress.name: precision
progress.description: Decimal point precision for calculated progress

progress.name: total
progress.description: Setting a total value will make each call to increment get closer to this total (i.e. 1/20, 2/20 etc)

progress.name: value
progress.description: Sets current value, when total is specified, this is used to calculate a ratio of the total, with percent this should be the overall percent

rating.name: initialRating
rating.description: A number representing the default rating to apply

rating.name: fireOnInit
rating.description: Whether callbacks like onRate should fire immediately after initializing with the current value.

rating.name: clearable
rating.description: By default a rating will be only clearable if there is 1 icon. Setting to true/false will allow or disallow a user to clear their rating

rating.name: interactive
rating.description: Whether to enable user's ability to rate

search.name: minCharacters
search.description: Minimum characters to query for results

search.name: transition
search.description: Named transition to use when animating menu in and out. Fade and slide down are available without including ui transitions

search.name: maxResults
search.description: Maximum results to display when using local and simple search, maximum category count for category search

search.name: cache
search.description: Caches results locally to avoid requerying server

search.name: source
search.description: Specify a Javascript object which will be searched locally

search.name: selectFirstResult
search.description: Whether the search should automatically select the first search result after searching

search.name: showNoResults
search.description: Whether a "no results" message should be shown if no results are found. (These messages can be modified using the template object specified below)

search.name: searchFullText
search.description: Return local results that match anywhere inside your content

search.name: fields
search.description: List mapping display content to JSON property, either with API or source.

search.name: searchFields
search.description: Specify object properties inside local source object which will be searched

search.name: hideDelay
search.description: Delay before hiding results after search blur

search.name: searchDelay
search.description: Delay before querying results on inputchange

search.name: easing
search.description: Easing equation when using fallback Javascript animation

shape.name: width
shape.description: When set to next will use the width of the next side during the shape's animation. When set to initial it will use the width of the shape at initialization. When set to a specifix pixel height, will force the width to that height.

shape.name: height
shape.description: When set to next will use the height of the next side during the shape's animation. When set to initial it will use the height of the shape at initialization. When set to a specifix pixel height, will force the height to that height.

sidebar.name: context
sidebar.description: Context which sidebar will appear inside

sidebar.name: exclusive
sidebar.description: Whether multiple sidebars can be open at once

sidebar.name: closable
sidebar.description: Whether sidebar can be closed by clicking on page

sidebar.name: dimPage
sidebar.description: Whether to dim page contents when sidebar is visible

sidebar.name: scrollLock
sidebar.description: Whether to lock page scroll when sidebar is visible

sidebar.name: returnScroll
sidebar.description: Whether to return to original scroll position when sidebar is hidden, automatically occurs with transition: scale

sidebar.name: delaySetup
sidebar.description: When sidebar is initialized without the proper HTML, using this option will defer creation of DOM to use requestAnimationFrame.

sidebar.name: transition
sidebar.description: Named transition to use when animating sidebar. Defaults to 'auto' which selects transition from defaultTransition based on direction.

sidebar.name: mobileTransition
sidebar.description: Named transition to use when animating when detecting mobile device. Defaults to 'auto' which selects transition from defaultTransitionbased on direction.

sidebar.name: defaultTransition
sidebar.description: Default transitions for each direction and screen size, used with transition: auto

sidebar.name: useLegacy
sidebar.description: Whether Javascript animations should be used. Defaults to false. Setting to auto will use legacy animations only for browsers that do not support CSS transforms

sidebar.name: duration
sidebar.description: Duration of sidebar animation when using legacy Javascript animation

sidebar.name: easing
sidebar.description: Easing to use when using legacy Javascript animation

sticky.name: pushing
sticky.description: Whether element should be "pushed" by the viewport, attaching to the bottom of the screen when scrolling up

sticky.name: jitter
sticky.description: Sticky container height will only be set if the difference between heights of container and context is larger than this jitter value.

sticky.name: observeChanges
sticky.description: Whether any change in context DOM should automatically refresh cached sticky positions

sticky.name: context
sticky.description: Context which sticky element should stick to

sticky.name: scrollContext
sticky.description: Context which sticky should attach onscroll events.

sticky.name: offset
sticky.description: Offset in pixels from the top of the screen when fixing element to viewport

sticky.name: bottomOffset
sticky.description: Offset in pixels from the bottom of the screen when fixing element to viewport

tab.name: auto
tab.description: Whether tab should load remote content as same url as history

tab.name: history
tab.description: Whether to record history events for tab changes

tab.name: ignoreFirstLoad
tab.description: Do not load content remotely on first tab load. Useful when open tab is rendered on server.

tab.name: evaluateScripts
tab.description: Whether inline scripts in tab HTML should be parsed on tab load. Defaults to once, parsing only on first load. Can also be set to true or false to always parse or never parse inline scripts.

tab.name: alwaysRefresh
tab.description: Tab should reload content every time it is opened

tab.name: deactivate
tab.description: Can be set to either siblings or all. Siblings will only de-activate tab activators that are siblings of the clicked element when a tab is selected. All will deactivate all other tab activators initialized at the same time.

tab.name: cacheType
tab.description: Can be set to either response or html. Response will cache the original response on load, this way callbacks always receive the same content. Using `html` will cache the resulting html after all callbacks, making sure any changes to content are preserved.

tab.name: cache
tab.description: Tab should cache content after loading locally to avoid server trip on second load

tab.name: historyType
tab.description: Can be set to hash or state. Hash will use an in-page link to create history events. State will use DOM History and load pages from server on refresh.

tab.name: path
tab.description: When using historyType state you must specify the base URL for all internal links.

tab.name: context
tab.description: Tabs are limited to those found inside this context

tab.name: childrenOnly
tab.description: If enabled limits tabs to children of passed context

tab.name: maxDepth
tab.description: Maximum amount of nested tabs allowed (avoids recursion)

transition.name: animation
transition.description: Named animation event to used. Must be defined in CSS.

transition.name: interval
transition.description: Interval in MS between each elements transition

transition.name: reverse
transition.description: When an interval is specified, sets order of animations. auto reverses only animations that are hiding.

transition.name: displayType
transition.description: Specify the final display type (block, inline-block etc) so that it doesn't have to be calculated.

transition.name: duration
transition.description: Duration of the CSS transition animation

transition.name: useFailSafe
transition.description: If enabled a timeout will be added to ensure animationend callback occurs even if element is hidden

transition.name: allowRepeats
transition.description: If enabled will allow same animation to be queued while it is already occurring

transition.name: queue
transition.description: Whether to automatically queue animation if another is occurring

visibility.name: once
visibility.description: When set to false a callback will occur each time an element passes the threshold for a condition.

visibility.name: continuous
visibility.description: When set to true a callback will occur anytime an element passes a condition not just immediately after the threshold is met.

visibility.name: type
visibility.description: Set to image to load images when on screen. Set to fixed to add class name fixed when passed.

visibility.name: initialCheck
visibility.description: Whether visibility conditions should be checked immediately on init

visibility.name: context
visibility.description: The scroll context visibility should use.

visibility.name: refreshOnLoad
visibility.description: Whether visibility conditions should be checked on window load. This ensures that after images load content positions will be updated correctly.

visibility.name: refreshOnResize
visibility.description: Whether visibility conditions should be checked on window resize. Useful when content resizes causes continuous changes in position

visibility.name: checkOnRefresh
visibility.description: Whether visibility conditions should be checked on calls to refresh. These calls can be triggered from either resize, load or manually calling $('.foo').visibility('refresh')

visibility.name: zIndex
visibility.description: Specify a z-index when using type: 'fixed'.

visibility.name: offset
visibility.description: Value that context scrollTop should be adjusted in pixels. Useful for making content appear below content fixed to the page.

visibility.name: includeMargin
visibility.description: Whether element calculations should include its margin

visibility.name: throttle
visibility.description: When set to an integer, scroll position will be debounced using this ms value. false will debounce with requestAnimationFrame.

visibility.name: observeChanges
visibility.description: Whether to automatically refresh content when changes are made to the element's DOM subtree

visibility.name: transition
visibility.description: When using type: image allows you to specify transition when showing a loaded image

visibility.name: duration
visibility.description: When using type: image allows you to specify transition duration
